  {\em CONCLUSION:} The drift of the reference potential explains the inconsistencies between the predictions of the models and the actual shapes of the EGs. The drift modifies the slopes of EG waveforms during excitation and recovery and can be expected to affect the assessment of excitation and recovery times and QRS and ST-T areas. Removing the drift reestablishes consistency between potential distributions and electrographic waveforms.},
